/// <br>
/// Its first few rows look like this:
///      1
///     1 1
///    1 2 1
///   1 3 3 1
/// where each element of each row is either 1 or the sum of the two elements right above it. 
/// <br>
/// For example, the next row of the triangle would be:
/// <span class="rosetta__text--indented">:: &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">1</span> &nbsp; (since the first element of each row doesn't have two elements above it)</span>
/// <span class="rosetta__text--indented">:: &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">4</span> &nbsp; (1 + 3)</span>
/// <span class="rosetta__text--indented">:: &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">6</span> &nbsp; (3 + 3)</span>
/// <span class="rosetta__text--indented">:: &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">4</span> &nbsp; (3 + 1)</span>
/// <span class="rosetta__text--indented">:: &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">1</span> &nbsp; (since the last element of each row doesn't have two elements above it) </span>
/// <br>
/// So the triangle now looks like this:
///      1
///     1 1
///    1 2 1
///   1 3 3 1
///  1 4 6 4 1
/// <br>
/// Each row &nbsp; <tt> n </tt> &nbsp; (starting with row &nbsp; 0 &nbsp; at the top) shows the coefficients of the binomial expansion of &nbsp; <big><big> (x + y)<sup>n</sup>. </big></big>
